metadata.name: Gerhard #410
metadata.description:
Gerhard is a collaboration of Richard Nadler and Leander Herzog on fxhash. A generative animation based on multiple layers of color and data, mixed, moved and painted over in realtime. Some fragments stick to the canvas while others get discarded to leave the existing layers visible, allowing a complex surface to emerge and build up over time. 
Richard Nadler created the textures to control composition and color. Leander Herzog created the code for the interplay between the layers, motion and interactions. Both artists use different tools and are not aware of the details of each others process, meeting through the interface of pixels. This collaboration is enabled by twitter and fxhash, as the generative art community continues to explore abstraction in summer 2022 ‚Äì while extreme temperatures, wildfires, ongoing conflicts and volatile markets continue to escalate. 

- Click to start a new layer of motion and color. 
- Doubleclick to enter fullscreen mode. 
- Press ‚Äús‚Äù to save the current canvas. 
- Append ?dpr=4 to the url to increase the resolution.

https://leanderherzog.ch/2022/gerhard/

metadata.name: Tenderness #30
metadata.description:
The lace aesthetic began to stir the minds of the public in the middle of the 20th century. With the light hand of Coco Chanel, the sexual revolution began to gain new traction, the consequence of which was the fashion designers' traditional idea of the beauty of the female female .

The images of the time absoluted the sexuality of the women. Every pattern, every curve and every hue was seen as something perfect, intriguing and hypnotic. The final touch of the "revolution" was the use of knitwear, which allowed the underwear to become even tighter and more provocative.

The idealized image of women in the dreams of men at that time was a vivid symbiosis of personality with elegant, feminine harmony, which embraces inspired the strongest individuals to create and to innovate.

Polina Arz ¬© 

A professional Fashion designer and fashion artist whose work reflects the spirit of modernity and the world around us in the language of current trends and contemporary art.

metadata.name: Uncrossed Paths #22
metadata.description:
Many agents start at random locations in random directions (up, down, left or right). There is a small chance that they might turn at any frame. Also, there is a small chance of a new agent being born perpendicular to any agent.
The ultimate rule is, the paths must not be crossed. If an agent comes across its own or another agent‚Äôs path, it turns and moves on. If there is no way to go, the agent stops.
The maximum animation time is 22 sec, although most of the token gets completed around 15 sec.
These simple rules, paired with some chosen palettes can generate beautiful figures.

Press r - restart the animation with different settings (primary traits stay the same)
Press s - save 2048x2048 png in live mode

metadata.name: Blueprints of balance #56
metadata.description:
Balance in art is one of the basic principles of design, along with contrast, movement, rhythm, emphasis, pattern, unity, and variety. Balance refers to how the elements of art (line, shape, color, value, space, form, texture) relate to each other within the composition in terms of their visual weight to create visual equilibrium. That is, one side does not seem heavier than another.

But there is no balance without Chaos. And that is why for one hour everyday each Blueprint of balance let it go and turns into its alternative wild version.
